cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper is about comparing citation counts of Microsoft Academic with Scopus and Mendeley for a set of journals from different specialisms. The paper focuses on scientometric research and data collection, which falls under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The study also involves analyzing citation patterns in different fields, which could be related to social networks (cs.SI) and cryptography (cs.CR).
